									  Investors					  

Investors
In 2011, Cloud Security Corporation turned its focus from general IT solutions to new market opportunities created by the massive explosion of remote location work environments, rapid expansion of network bandwidth, and a surge in the everyday use of smartphones, tablet PCs and netbooks that are increasingly part of remote-location – and even on-premise – business.  This Bring-Your-Own-Device (BYOD) proliferation has given rise to a host of new security issues – the focus of CLDS.
In 2012, Cloud Security Corporation (then Cloud Star Corporation) went public under the symbol: CLDS. With security now being the major component of the Company’s business model, Cloud Security Corporation is dedicated to capitalizing on security trends in the cloud and BYOD. For more information on our products or services, as well as development status or opportunities, please feel free to contact the number below.
Investor Relations
