eSecurityPlanet > Products > Microsoft Cloud App Security: CASB Product Overview and Insight

							Microsoft Cloud App Security: CASB Product Overview and Insight						








                                                            By Paul Rubens,
                                
                                Posted July 25, 2017                        

We review Microsoft Cloud App Security CASB, including the cloud security product's use cases, notable features, security qualifications and supported applications.




SHARE   





 







 














 







 




 





 SHARE 







 











 






















 











 





See our complete list of top CASB vendors.
Company information
Microsoft's CASB product stems from the company's acquisition of Adallom in 2015. Adallom started shipping in early 2013.
Target market
Enterprises and small to medium size organizations.
Notable Features
As part of Enterprise Mobility + Security (EMS), Cloud App Security builds on Microsoft's broader security platform and works together with other identity and security solutions, including Azure Active Directory, Microsoft Advanced Threat Analytics, Microsoft Intune and Azure Information Protection. Additionally, it is deeply integrated with Office 365, providing security management and transparency capabilities.
Supported cloud applications
Office 365, Box, Okta, Google Apps, AWS, Service Now, Salesforce, Dropbox.
Industry strengths
Applicable across all verticals.
Security qualifications
CSA Star Certification, EU Model Clauses, EU-U.S. Privacy Shield, FISC, HIPAA/HITECH, ISO 9001, ISO 22301, ISO 27001, ISO 27018, PCI DSS, UK G-Cloud.
Method of delivery
Cloud.
Technology (API, proxy or hybrid):
Cloud App Security is available through API deployment. A proxy (in-session control) deployment option is in Private Preview.
Pricing
Cloud App Security is available for purchase as a subscription for $5 per user per month as the estimated retail price. It is also a component of Microsoft Mobility + Security E5.
CASB revenues
Not disclosed.
Approximate number of paying customers
Not disclosed.




 
