SecureAuth - New Adaptive Authentication






 



  








Prevent the Misuse of Stolen CredentialsSecureAuth IdP: An on-premises adaptive access platform that offers multi-factor and adaptive authentication, single sign-on, user self-service and unmatched flexible workflows in a single product.SecureAuth Cloud Access: enables you to securely manage SaaS adoption while having the agility to adapt to your organization’s dynamic demands. Get the convenience of secure single sign-on (SSO) to over 8,000 applications.Get a Demo
 <iframe src="http://www2.secureauth.com/18252/2017-03-08/7xm81b" width="100%" height="350" type="text/html" frameborder="0" allowTransparency="true" style="border: 0"></iframe>

 SecureAuth, whether on premises, in the Cloud or both, provides flexible, industry-leading identity and access management, Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) and Single Sign-On (SSO) solutions using multi-layered Adaptive Authentication risk checks creating an invisible layer of security with a frictionless user experience. SecureAuth IdP: An on-premises adaptive access platform that offers multi-factor and adaptive authentication, single sign-on, user self-service and unmatched flexible workflows in a single product.SecureAuth Cloud Access: enables you to securely manage SaaS adoption while having the agility to adapt to your organization’s dynamic demands. Get the convenience of secure single sign-on (SSO) to over 8,000 applications.Get a Demo
 <iframe src="http://www2.secureauth.com/l/18252/2017-03-08/7xm81b" width="100%" height="550" type="text/html" frameborder="0" allowTransparency="true" style="border: 0"></iframe>

Frictionless, flexible, pain-free - SecureAuth protects, detects & prevents like no one else can.Multi-Factor Authentication - Over 25 Methods10+ Modern Adaptive Authentication Defense LayersSecure Single Sign-On (SSO)User Self-ServiceDig Deeper into the Layers:Get a DemoSecureAuth Modern Adaptive Authentication Defense LayersReal-Time Security Without Impacting UsabilityDevice RecognitionEnsures the device being used is known and recognizable.Threat ServiceAnalyzes IP addresses of incoming access requests for known bad IPs and malicious behavior.Directory LookupDouble-checks the user’s identity profile against a known directory.Geo-LocationCompares a user's login location against known locations for employees, partners and customers.Geo-VelocityKeeps an eye out for access requests spanning different locations that aren't physically possible.Geo-FencingTreat access requests coming from within and outside a customer-defined geographic barrier differently.Phone # Fraud PreventionBlock access requests from ported phones, carriers, and phone types (e.g. Mobile, Landline, VoIP, etc.)Behavioral BiometricsThwarts attacks by using user keystrokes and mouse movements for a unique behavioral signature.Identity GovernanceIdentify users with high-risk access rights and adapt authentication to protect this vulnerability.User & Entity BehaviorTreat access requests differently when user behavior strays from the normal.Customer Success Stories"[SecureAuth] worked with not only our main Citrix-based application, but all other types of different applications, from VPN to web reverse proxy to cloud-based SaaS apps. It was a home run in every category" "The ability for us to utilize the enhanced functionality of SecureAuth in order to provide better user experience in terms of ways to authenticate, ways to fingerprint someone, really was an easy cost justification..." "SecureAuth is used to protect sensitive data both internally and externally to our network. SecureAuth is also leveraged to protect systems/applications used around the world by both our corporate and retail employees." Copyright© 2017 SecureAuth All Rights Reserved
